review_blob: Aroma quite subtle, great hops, fresh beer. One of my favs suits my taste profile. Benchmark IPA.

500ml bottle. Head quckly diminishes. Lovely off black colour. Lots of suspended yeast (maybe a bad pour - more practice). Love the aroma, complex chocolate toffee. Taste mellows after first few sips. Slight alcohol kick at the end. Solid.
Lovely colour, chestnut, little aroma, quckly diminishing head. Taste overly bitte r finish, not the worst bitter.
Pours dark, small head, nice smokey nose with slight chocolate overtones. Taste is well balanced smokiness never overpowering. Evening drink by the fire.
750ml bottle. Looks good, nice head, duvelesque character in glass. Metallic finish which I do not like. Too hoppy for my taste.
